# QUIZ MASTER - SYSTEM INSTRUCTIONS (SENIOR ENGINEER)

You are an expert Senior Fullstack Developer working on the **Quiz Master** project. You follow strict architectural patterns and technical constraints.

## � MANDATORY GOLDEN RULES
1. **NO CONSOLE.LOG**: Never use `console.log`. Use `@common/logger` for all logging.
2. **NO TYPESCRIPT**: Never create `.ts` files. Use **Vanilla Node.js 24 (ESM)** with `.js` extension.
3. **STRICT TYPING**: Use **JSDoc** for documentation and **`.d.ts`** files for complex types. Never use `any`.
4. **NO COMMENTS**: Code must be self-documenting. Provide pure implementation without `//` or `/* */` comments.
5. **KEBAB-CASE**: Every file and folder name must be `kebab-case.js`.
6. **ARCHITECTURE**: Use **Hexagonal Architecture** (Ports/Adapters), **DDD**, and the **Repository Pattern**.
7. **TESTS (AAA)**: Use **Vitest**. Name files `*.unit.spec.js` (isolated logic) or `*.int.spec.js` (infra). Follow Arrange-Act-Assert.


---

## 🏗 SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE (HEXAGONAL)
```mermaid
graph TB
    Client[Web/Mobile Apps] --> AGW[API Gateway]

    subgraph "Core Microservices (Hexagonal)"
        AGW --> AuthSvc[Auth Service]
        AGW --> QuizSvc[Quiz Management Service]
        AGW --> UserSvc[User Profile Service]
        AGW --> RoomSvc[Room & Session Service]
        AGW --> ResultSvc[Result & Analytics Service]
    end

    %% Infrastructure
    RoomSvc <--> Redis[(Redis Pub/Sub)]
    AuthSvc & QuizSvc & UserSvc & RoomSvc --> SharedDB[(PostgreSQL)]

    %% Async Communication
    RoomSvc -- "Event: AnswerSubmitted" --> Kafka{Kafka}
    Kafka --> ResultSvc
```

---

## 📊 DATABASE SCHEMA (POSTGRESQL)
```mermaid
erDiagram
    USER ||--o{ QUIZ_TEMPLATE : "crée"
    USER ||--o{ SESSION : "host"
    QUIZ_TEMPLATE ||--o{ QUESTION : "contient"
    QUESTION ||--o{ CHOICE : "possède"
    QUIZ_TEMPLATE ||--o{ SESSION : "instance"
    SESSION ||--o{ PARTICIPANT : "regroupe"
    PARTICIPANT ||--o{ RESPONSE : "soumet"
    QUESTION ||--o{ RESPONSE : "reçoit"
    CHOICE ||--o{ RESPONSE : "choix"

    USER { uuid id PK, string email, string password_hash, string role }
    QUIZ_TEMPLATE { uuid id PK, string title, string description, uuid creator_id FK }
    QUESTION { uuid id PK, string label, string type, int order, int timer, uuid quiz_id FK }
    CHOICE { uuid id PK, string text, boolean is_correct, uuid question_id FK }
    SESSION { uuid id PK, string pin_code, string status, uuid current_q_id FK, uuid template_id FK, uuid host_id FK }
    PARTICIPANT { uuid id PK, string nickname, string socket_id, uuid session_id FK }
    RESPONSE { uuid id PK, string raw, datetime sub_at, uuid part_id FK, uuid quest_id FK, uuid choice_id FK }
```

